2^n
\sum_{n=1}^{2^n} \frac{1}{n} = 1+\sum_{k=0}^n\sum_{l=0}^{2^{k-1}-1} \frac{1}{2^k+l}
\sum_{k=0}^n\sum_{l=0}^{2^{k-1}-1} \frac{1}{2^k+l} \geq \sum_{k=0}^n\sum_{l=0}^{2^{k-1}-1} \frac{1}{2^k} = \sum_{k=0}^n \frac{1}{2}=\frac{n+1}{2}
f(x)= \frac{1}{x^2}
\sum_{n=2}^N \frac{1}{n^2} = \sum_{n=2}^N f(n) \leq \int_1^{N-1} f(x) dx = 1-\frac{1}{N-1}
